commit.message:
Ignore DisallowedHost errors on Django's Request.get_host()

If we are about to log DisallowedHost errors, we cannot use
django.http.request.Request.get_host() to get the request's host as it
would an DisallowedHost exception again.
So handle this exception and fallback directly to the HOST header.

Remove pypy from Travis builds and skip PyLint for Python 2.7

Travis' Ubuntu 18.04 image doesn't provide pypy and pypy3, so skip
these environments.
Use PyLint as well for linting

Flush all pending events on shutdown

When cleanly shutting down, fetch queued events from the database and
send them to Logstash as long as there events.
This prevents stalling events in the database in much logging but short
running applications.
Enable more Python versions for tests

Close TCP socket on connect timeouts

Previously, the already created socket was leaked and not closed
properly if the connection timed out already on connect.
